last_episode_to_air.name: Aunt Emma Visits the Wilsons
last_episode_to_air.overview: When Mr. Wilson's Aunt Emma pays a visit she takes an instant liking to Dennis, causing Mr. Wilson to fear she will make Dennis her heir.

name: Dennis the Menace
overview: This 1959-1963 television situation comedy series follows the lives of the Mitchell family, Henry, Alice, and their only child Dennis, an energetic, trouble-prone, mischievous, but well-meaning boy, who often tangles with his peace-and-quiet-loving neighbor George Wilson, a retired salesman, or, later, with George's brother John, a writer. Dennis is basically a good, well-intentioned boy who always tries to help people, but who winds up making situations worse â€“ often at Mr. Wilson's expense.

episodes.name: Dennis Goes to the Movies
episodes.overview: Dennis eludes a babysitter to go to the movies that his parents are at.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Signpost
episodes.overview: Dennis replaces a fallen signpost... backwards.

episodes.name: The Fishing Trip
episodes.overview: Henry and Mr.Wilson try to go fishing without Dennis.

episodes.name: Grandpa and Miss Cathcart
episodes.overview: Dennis tries to fix his Grampa Perkins up with Miss Cathcart.

episodes.name: Innocents in Space
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson thinks he has discovered a space satellite.

episodes.name: Dennis' Garden
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson's garden originally consisted of Dahlia bulbs. When Dennis sees them, he thinks they are ""sweet potatoes"" and after    his bedtime, he ""secretly exchanges"" what is in his garden with   what is in Mr. Wilson's garden.    Dennis eventually raises the Dahlia bulbs & wins a 1st prize    medal. After the garden judges see Mr. Wilson's garden, he is also given a medal.

episodes.name: The New Neighbors
episodes.overview: Dennis helps Mr Wilson sell a neighbors house.

episodes.name: Tenting Tonight
episodes.overview: Dennis and Tommy camp out in the back yard.   Dennis' parents friends The Melton's play a    record containing wild animal sounds to entertain   the boys while they are camping out in the yard.   Mr. Wilson can hear the record from his house and   is convinced that wild animals have escaped from the    circus and are after the boys so Mr. Wilson goes out    to the yard to try and save Dennis and Tommy from danger.

episodes.name: Dennis Sells Bottles
episodes.overview: Dennis thinks his dad is broke so he sells bottles   to try and help his dad out. However, when Dennis tells   some of the neighbors what he is doing the neighbors get   the wrong idea about the Mitchell's and think that they   are in trouble financially.

episodes.name: Mr. Wilson's Award
episodes.overview: Dennis starts a rumor that him and his family are moving to New York only to keep Mr. Wilson in town to get his award.

episodes.name: The Christmas Story (aka Dennis & Christmas)
episodes.overview: Dennis is going crazy trying to find his gifts.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Cowboy
episodes.overview: Dennis meets Whip Crawford his cowboy idol after Mrs Webster tells Dennis he will be in the play.

episodes.name: Dennis Haunts a House
episodes.overview: Dennis Haunts Mr. Wilson's house due to him and his   friends starting a club house in Mr. Wilson's   basement.

episodes.name: Dennis' Tree House
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson attempts to teach Dennis about   bird watching, then Dennis takes care of   a sick bird

episodes.name: Dennis and the Rare Coin
episodes.overview: George Wilson is looking for a rare coin. But George is in for a sad shock $250.00 (that's what he paid for the coin) But the coin is fake!

episodes.name: Dennis and the Bike
episodes.overview: To get a bike Dennis sells a fishbowl of beans which he has to count before 5pm!

episodes.name: Dennis and the Open House
episodes.overview: The Mitchell's are having a party and the guests are late, So Dennis tries to help people find the house by taking an open House for Free!

episodes.name: Dennis and the Duck
episodes.overview: Dennis's duck (George) causes problems for Mr. Willson who is running for The Garden Club. He tries to get the duck to the lake.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Swing
episodes.overview: Henry tries to take Alice out on their Anniversary.   Meanwhile Dennis tries to build a swing in his yard   and ends up chasing a cat up a tree in the process.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Dog
episodes.overview: Dennis cares for a dog named Charlie who wins a prize for his painting!

episodes.name: Mr. Wilson's Sister
episodes.overview: Dennis meets Helen and wants to be pirate.

episodes.name: Dennis and the TV Set
episodes.overview: Dennis goes to any length to get a TV and turns Mr. Wilson's tv on!

episodes.name: Dennis Creates a Hero
episodes.overview: Dennis asks a reporter to write a story about his dad with hopes of getting his picture in the paper.

episodes.name: Dennis' Paper Drive
episodes.overview: Mrs Holland tells Dennis that anyone who collets the most newspapers will win a silver dollar made in 1895 that is worth $600 which catces Mr. Wilson's eye.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Bees
episodes.overview: Dennis learns Opie might leave because his bees have no honey. Dennis sprays prfume on Mr. Willison's flowers.

episodes.name: Alice's Birthday
episodes.overview: Dennis puts a sign in Mr. Finch's store telling everybody not forget his mom's Birthday.

episodes.name: Dennis Becomes a Baby Sitter
episodes.overview: Dennis's parents hire a baby sitter while his parents entertain business client. Dennis is a baby sitter to Michael Bouchet, was asked to stay with Dennis.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Starlings
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson has a bunch of starlings in his tree and wants   to get rid of them. Dennis eventually gets rid of the   starlings by putting liver in Mr. Wilson's tree which attracts   a lot of cats.

episodes.name: The Party Line
episodes.overview: The Driscolls are new neighbors but the Driscoll's phone is on the same line as the mitchell's.

episodes.name: Dennis by Proxy
episodes.overview: Dennis builds a bench for Mr. Dorfamn to sit on.

episodes.name: Dennis Runs Away
episodes.overview: Dennis tries to walk to his Grandpa's house   and the police stop him and try to figure   out who he is.

episodes.name: Miss Cathcart's Sunsuit
episodes.overview: Dennis sells Valentine's Day cards in July to by swim fins,   which end up causing a run on Valentine's day cards around   the entire neighborhood.

episodes.name: Out of Retirement
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson gets a visit from his former boss who   offers him his job back in Pittsburgh. When Dennis   thinks Mr. Wilson is moving to Pittsburgh, he runs away   from home.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Wedding
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson's Niece is getting married   and asks Dennis to be the ring bear.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Radio Set
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson gives Dennis an old radio set   that he mistakenly bid for at an auction.   However, When Dennis finds money in his    radio set, Mr. Wilson gets excited. So him   and Mitchell put in add in the paper hoping   the real owner isn't around to claim it.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Ham-pher
episodes.overview: Dennis gets what he thinks is a hampster which turns out    to be a gopher that escapes from his cage and almost ruins   Mr. Wilson's yard.

episodes.name: The Stock Certificate
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson has a stock certificate worth $500.   He hides it in his Phone book, however when Dennis    brings him in his new phone book Mr. Wilson goes   crazy and ends up going to the warehouse where all   the old phonebooks are taken to look for his old   phone book because he thinks the stock is still in it.

episodes.name: Man of the House
episodes.overview: Dennis tries to take care of his mom because she is sick and his   dad is out of town.

episodes.name: The Rock Collection
episodes.overview: Dennis starts a rock collection and ends up finding   what he thinks is real gold on Mr. Wilson's lot

episodes.name: Henry and Togetherness
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson tricks Mr. Mitchell out of playing golf to spend   more time with Dennis.

episodes.name: Paint-up, Clean-up Week
episodes.overview: Dennis wants to help out for Paint-up, Clean-up week.   So Mr. Wilson gives Dennis a bucket of red paint to   paint his wagon with. Dennis however also decides to   paint the street curve by Mr. Wilson's house and Mr.   Wilson gets blamed for it.

episodes.name: Dennis Learns to Whistle
episodes.overview: Dennis is very upset because he doesn't know how to   whistle, So he spends all day trying to learn how.

episodes.name: The Raffle Ticket
episodes.overview: Dennis gets an electric car for his mom from the lady   who won the Raffle.

episodes.name: The Christmas Horse
episodes.overview: Dennis is determined to get a horse for Christmas, So on Christmas day he goes around the neighborhood trying to find   what he thinks is his horse.

episodes.name: Dennis' Allowance
episodes.overview: Dennis is trying to learn about how to earn money by working.   His dad eventually starts him on an allowance.

episodes.name: Dennis' Penny Collection
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson Helps Dennis start a penny collection,   However Mr. Wilson fears that Dennis having a penny   collection is going to be trouble to him.

episodes.name: Dennis, the Campaign Manager
episodes.overview: Dennis convinces Mr. Wilson to run for park commissioner   because the playgroung is closed except on weekends.

episodes.name: Miss Cathcart's Friend
episodes.overview: Dennis attempts to find Miss. Cathcart a best friend, so   he gets her a dog from the pound. However the dog's owner   is looking for him and ends up showing up at Miss. Cathcart's   house before Dennis brings the dog over to Miss. Cathcart.   So she mistakenly thinks that the guy is the friend instead of the dog.

episodes.name: Pythias Was a Piker
episodes.overview: Dennis writes a composition for school on his best   friend and he chooses Mr. Wilson to write about.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Saxophone
episodes.overview: Tommy has a saxophone that he doesn't want so Dennis   wants to buy it from Tommy's Mother, but when Mr. Wilson   learns that Dennis is going to ask his father to buy it   for him Mr. Wilson tries to talk Dennis's dad out of   getting the saxophone.

episodes.name: Wilson Sleeps Over
episodes.overview: Dennis accidently knocks over a bottle which fumigates   the Wilson's house, So the Wilson's stay the night at   the Mitchell's and Mr. Wilson walks in his sleep.

episodes.name: Dennis' Birthday
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson puts on a magic show for Dennis' birthday   and asks Spring Byington to be his assistant

episodes.name: Dennis Goes to Camp
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson takes Dennis and his friends to a camp   to visit for a day and end up getting stranded there   for a week because a bridge went out due to a storm.

episodes.name: Dennis' Tool Chest
episodes.overview: Miss Cathcart's cat is accidentally locked in the trunk of Mr. Wilson's car.

episodes.name: The Going Away Gift
episodes.overview: Dennis gets his mom a going away present and hides it on   Mr. Wilson's closet shelf and Mrs. Wilson finds it and thinks   it's a gift from Mr. Wilson.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Fishing Rod
episodes.overview: Dennis attempts to buy a fishing rod for his dad   and tries to purchase it with a $50.00 Confederate bill.

episodes.name: Dennis' Obligation
episodes.overview: Dennis brings home little chicken eggs to take care of   for his school project, but ends up taking them over to   Mr. Wilson's house because the Mitchell's electricity   went out.

episodes.name: The Dog Trainer
episodes.overview: Dennis trains Mr. Wilson's dog Fremont, which backfires when   Fremont will only listen to Dennis and ignores Mr. Wilson.

episodes.name: Woodman, Spare That Tree
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson has a hundred doller bill which he drops and a crow   picks it up and flies away with it. He later finds it in an old   tree in a park which the park commissioner is going to cut down,   So Mr. Wilson climbs the tree to get his hundred doller bill and   to also save the tree from being cut down.

episodes.name: The Boy Wonder
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson builds a barbecue in his backyard with help   from Dennis' friend, Fred Bains.

episodes.name: The Soapbox Derby
episodes.overview: Dennis enters a soapbox derby and Mr. Wilson accidently ends up    being the one driving it in the race.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Camera
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson is supposed to take a picture of a plant that bloomes   at night but ends up dozing off when it bloomes, So Dennis takes   the picture of the plant for him.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Miracle Plant Food
episodes.overview: Dennis accidently steps on one of Mr. Wilson's plants and so he   buys him a replacement and plants it in Mr. Wilson's flower bed.   When Mr. Wilson sees it, he is convinced that his new miracle   plant food that he invented works like a miracle.

episodes.name: Dennis' Newspaper
episodes.overview: Dennis overhears Mr. Wilson saying that he wishes he had his   racoon coat back, so he gives the story to the newspaper and   so all day people are bringing Mr. Wilson racoon coats.

episodes.name: Mr. Wilson's Paradise
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson wants to go to Mexico to the Island of Happiness but   changes his mind when he hears that his Neice is going to have a   baby at the time when he was going to go.

episodes.name: The Fortune Cookie
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson gets a fortune cookie of which sais ""Beware Of Tomorrow"" and so he is convinced that the fortune will come   true.

episodes.name: The Pioneers
episodes.overview: Dennis, Mr. Wilson, Mr. Mitchell camp out as pioneers   to prove to Mr. Krinkie that they can live of the land   like the pioneers.

episodes.name: Father's Day for Mr. Wilson
episodes.overview: Dennis decides to give Mr. Wilson his own father's day,   Which in the end turns out for the best when Dennis gets   Mr. Wilson out of a lawsuit concerning his dog, Fremont.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Picnic
episodes.overview: Henry finds a bag of money in the rain gutter, So he calls   Mr. Wilson and they take it to the police station. They later   learn that the money is counterfeit.

episodes.name: Trouble from Mars
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson accidentlly gets a space helmet that belongs to   Dennis stuck on his head.

episodes.name: Best Neighbor
episodes.overview: Dennis and Mr. Wilson camp out on a moutain so that Dennis can   join the Junior Pathfinders club.

episodes.name: Keep Off the Grass
episodes.overview: Henry gets a ticket for walking on the grass in the park.   When Mr. Wilson hears about it he thinks it isn't fair, So   he convinces Henry to go to court and contest it.

episodes.name: Mr. Wilson's Safe
episodes.overview: Dennis is using numbers for a football play which is the combination to Mr. Wilson's safe, So Mr. Wilson and Henry   get Dennis so confused that he forgets the combination.   Then Mr. Wilson forgets it. Now they are in a real mess   because Mr. Wilson has something very important locked in   the safe. So Mr. Wilson tries everything including trying   to hypnotize Dennis so he can remember the combination. He ends up hypnotizing himself and remembers the combination at last.

episodes.name: Haunted House
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson and Henry both invest in a house that   is known to be a haunted house.

episodes.name: The School Play
episodes.overview: Dennis' school is putting on a play which Mr. Wilson ends up   being in (not by choice) because him and Tommy (who is also   in the play) get handcuffed together before the play starts.

episodes.name: The Fifty-Thousandth Customer
episodes.overview: Mr. Finch is having a contest that when the fifty-thousandth   customer walks in his store they will win 5 minutes of   free shopping of which Mr. Wilson is determined to be the   one who wins.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Pee Wee League
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson coaches Dennis' Pee Wee League baseball team   because Dennis' dad (who originally was the coach) got sick.

episodes.name: Mr. Wilson's Inheritance
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson wants to represent Scotland for Dennis' School

episodes.name: Dennis Is a Genius
episodes.overview: The school test scores mistake Dennis as a genius.

episodes.name: The Lucky Piece
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson tricks Dennis into taking a silver coin that says   GOOD LUCK and a horseshoe on it instead of 50 cents that he owes him for cutting his lawn. Mrs. Wilson is very angry with him about it. So, she and Alice start a scheme of their own by making lucky things happen to Dennis all day. Mr. Wilson soon   starts to believe that the coin was lucky after all and is   sorry he ever let it go. He then realizes that it was all a    charade to teach him a lesson.

episodes.name: The Fifteen Foot Christmas Tree
episodes.overview: Dennis, Henry and Mr. Wilson go out in the woods and cut   down a big Christmas tree which ends up getting   almost destroyed by the time they get it home.

episodes.name: Dennis' Bank Account
episodes.overview: Dennis opens a bank account at the bank of where   Mr. Wilson works at and causes a lot of chaos at the bank.

episodes.name: Through Thick and Thin
episodes.overview: Dennis' cub scouts are putting on a circus of which   Mr. Wilson is the Lion in the circus, which is suppose   to be a secret from everyone.

episodes.name: Calling All Bird Lovers
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson holds a bird lovers session at his home   Where a woman does bird calls that sounds just like   a bird.

episodes.name: Silence Is Golden
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson agrees to give Dennis his magnifying glass   if he doesn't talk around him for the day.

episodes.name: Dennis Has a Fling
episodes.overview: Dennis is put on the spot when he askes both Mr. Wilson and   Mr. Mactavish to represent Scotland in his school project.

episodes.name: Frog Jumping Contest
episodes.overview: Dennis enters his frog in the frog jumping contest    with Mr. Wilson as his partner who has a bet with   Sgt. Mooney that Dennis' frog will beat his.

episodes.name: Where There's a Will
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson gives Dennis a Gold watch in his will.   Soon after that Mr. Wilson begins to feel old and is   convinced that he has short time to live.

episodes.name: Mr. Wilson's Uncle
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson's Uncle comes to visit him and convinces him that he   isn't in shape, so he starts a physical fitness program and   forces Mr. Mitchell and Mr. Wilson to be in it.

episodes.name: The Private Eye
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson gets his wallet taken by a pick pocket, So Dennis   and Tommy try to find the crook for the police.

episodes.name: Mr. Wilson's Housekeeper
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson hires a housekeeper for Mrs. Wilson but soon   regrets it when the housekeeper tries to tell Mr. Wilson   what he can and can't do in his home. Mr. Wilson then    tries to get rid of her.

episodes.name: A Dog's Life
episodes.overview: A big shaggy dog followes Mr. Wilson home and Mr. Wilson   tries to get rid of it.

episodes.name: Dennis' Documentary Film
episodes.overview: Dennis does a documentary film of the town for   a school project with Mr. Wilson's help.

episodes.name: Horseless Carriage Club
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson takes Dennis and his friends up to the lake   and back in an old car. Mr. Wilson then gets elected president   of the Horseless Carriage Club.

episodes.name: Junior Pathfinders Ride Again
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson attempts to start a fire like the pioneers did   for Dennis' Junior Pathfinders club and nearly burns down   the place.

episodes.name: The Treasure Chest
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson buys a treasure chest at an auction   thinking that it has buried treasure in it. Mr. Wilson   later discovers a treasure map drawn by Dennis. Although   Mr. Wilson thinks the map is authentic so he plans to   take a trip to the island and dig for the treasure.

episodes.name: Wilson Goes to the Dentist
episodes.overview: Dennis convinces Mr. Wilson to go to the Dentist for his   tooth because Dennis thinks he can get a basketball from   the Dentist until he learns that the Dentist only gives   away prizes to child patients.

episodes.name: The Man Next Door
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson thinks his next door neighbor is the stocking    bandit and tries to prove it.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Dodger
episodes.overview: Mr. Quigley coaches Dennis' baseball team with help from Sandy Koufax.

episodes.name: Dennis' Lovesick Friend
episodes.overview: Dennis helps Mr. Wilson's Uncle Ned plant flower bulbs in his yard in order to get out of playing house with Margaret Wade.

episodes.name: John Wilson's Cushion
episodes.overview: George Wilson's brother John Wilson comes to visit, only he has trouble working without his old cushion.

episodes.name: John Wilson Wins a Chicken
episodes.overview: Dennis and his friends win John Wilson a chicken, which John   wants to cook for dinner and the children try to talk him out of it.

episodes.name: The Bully
episodes.overview: Dennis is all set for a big day.  He is scheduled to have a fight with Gifford - the school bully.

episodes.name: The Club Initiation
episodes.overview: Dennis wants to join an older boys club, but in order to   do so he has to take an initiation.

episodes.name: Community Picnic
episodes.overview: The Neighborhood Community puts on a carnival in the park with different winning contests to participate in.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Witch Doctor
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson is doing a magazine article on voodoo, Dennis    gets the wrong idea and tells the whole neighborhood that   Mr. Wilson is a Witch Doctor, Soon the whole town gets the   wrong idea about Mr. Wilson.

episodes.name: The Chinese Girl
episodes.overview: Mr. and Mrs. Wilson have a Chinese girl that is staying with them   while Mr. Wilson is interviewing the girls father for a magazine   article.

episodes.name: You Go Your Way
episodes.overview: Dennis hears Mr.& Mrs. Wilson argue and spreads it around the   Neighborhood and soon some of the neighbors think that the   Wilson's have split up.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Circular Circumstances
episodes.overview: Dennis gets a job for a day delivering Circulars for Mrs. Elkins.   But, When he swaps territories with another kid, he gets blamed   for throwing the circulars in a trash can.

episodes.name: The Little Judge
episodes.overview: It's Children's Day in Court, and Dennis is the Judge! Mr Wilson goes to court to dispute a ticket he received for violating a city ordinance.

episodes.name: Poor Mr. Wilson
episodes.overview: Dennis thinks that Mr. Wilson is broke so he tries tries to help   him out.

episodes.name: Dennis in Gypsyland
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson gets mixed up with Gypsyes and they think he   is one of them.

episodes.name: The New Principal
episodes.overview: Dennis gets a new Principal, Mr. Spivey who is very strict at his   school. Mr. Spivey and Dennis get off on the wrong foot at first   However, Johnny Brady takes note of that and because he wants to be on the pitcher on the school baseball team. So, he sets Dennis up by drawling a picture on the back of his paper making fun Mr. Spivey's height. When Mr. Spivey finds it he naturally assumes Dennis is the one that drew it so he punishes Dennis by   kicking him off the baseball team and keeping him after school.   As the news travels Mr. Wilson, Mr. Quigley and Mr. Finch all go   to the school a few minutes apart and talk to Mr. Spivey each claiming to be Henry Mitchell to stand up for Dennis. Mr. Spivey   gets confused but soon realizes he misjudged Dennis and ends up apologizing and putting Dennis back on the school baseball team.

episodes.name: San Diego Safari
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson gets a chimpanzee from the San Diego zoo   which causes chaos at the Motel that the Wilsons and   the Mitchells are staying at.

episodes.name: Dennis at Boot Camp
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson's nephew visits him and gives Mr. Wilson and    Dennis a ride in his navy truck and then Mr. wilson and    Dennis get trapped on the navy base.

episodes.name: Henry's New Job
episodes.overview: Henry is thinking of getting a new job which takes   place neer the Asian river. Dennis does what he can   to prevent it including running away from home.

episodes.name: Wilson's Second Childhood
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson hangs out and plays with Dennis and his friends the   whole day to gather information for a magazine article of what   young children do in this day and age.

episodes.name: Jane Butterfield Says
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson is doing a column for the newspaper that he thinks will have every single women in town happily Married. However,   it ends up getting Sgt. Mooney in a love triangle with Miss   Cathcart and Miss Tarbell.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Hermit
episodes.overview: Dennis visits a hermit out in the woods, Mr. Wilson thinks that   he fought in the civil war, so he tries to get his life story.

episodes.name: My Uncle Ned
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson has written a book on his Uncle Ned's life for his   publisher. Uncle Ned however does not want the book to be published So Mr. Wilson goes up to Uncle Ned's house to try and   reason with him. The only thing is that Uncle ned has gone down    to Mr. Wilson's house to talk with him as well. Now it is up to   Dennis to try and keep Uncle Ned from meeting the publisher until   Mr. Wilson can return home again.

episodes.name: Junior Astronaut
episodes.overview: Dennis' School has a contest that any student who collects   the most stamps wins a trip to Cape Canaveral and meet an   Astronaut. Unfortunately, Dennis comes down with the chicken pox    right when he is about to win.

episodes.name: Wilson's Little White Lie
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson tells Dennis he isn't feeling well to get Dennis   to leave him alone and then Dennis tells the whole neighborhood,   So they all think that Mr. Wilson is very sick.

episodes.name: Dennis, the Rain Maker
episodes.overview: Dennis and his friends do an indian rain dance to try to   get Henry out of playing golf with his boss.

episodes.name: The Creature with the Big Feet
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson thinks he has discovered big-foot prints in his   yard which end with hilarity results.

episodes.name: Dennis, the Confused Cupid
episodes.overview: Dennis becomes confused about love when he hears his   parents and Mr.& Mrs. Wilson argue with one another.

episodes.name: Dennis Goes to Washington
episodes.overview: Dennis is appointed by the Mayor to go to Washington   and ask the Senater to pass a bill for a national   Forest.

episodes.name: The Big Basketball Game
episodes.overview: Dennis and his friends help a boy who is poor and feels that he   doesn't fit in prepare for and play in the school basketball game.

episodes.name: Wilson's Allergy
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson is convinced that he is allergic to Dennis   because he sneezes every time Dennis is around. It is   later discovered that it was only the hair tonic that   Dennis had been using what was causing Mr. Wilson's allergies.

episodes.name: Baby Booties
episodes.overview: Dennis sees baby booties knitted for Mr. Wilson's golf clubs   and he thinks that the Wilson's are having a baby, So he   goes around and tells the whole neighborhood.

episodes.name: My Four Boys
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson enters a contest that requires having children,   so he passes Dennis and his friends off as his kids.

episodes.name: Dennis and the Homing Pigeons
episodes.overview: Dennis accidentally ties an important note that belongs to Mr. Wilson on a pigeon, so Mr. Wilson, Henry, Tommy and Dennis go   to where the pigeons roost at night at a spooky house to try and get the note back and end up in the middle of a collage fraternity initiation meant for new fraternity members. After   a bunch of twists and turns they find the pigeon with the note tied on it.

episodes.name: A Tax on Cats
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson becomes a cat catcher for the police department   to try and enforce a cat leash law.

episodes.name: The Uninvited Guest
episodes.overview: Dennis stays at the Wilson's house overnight while his   parents are out of town which turns out to be a long night   for everyone with different incidents.

episodes.name: Dennis Plays Robin Hood
episodes.overview: Dennis and his friends decide to play Robin Hood and help   Mr. Wilson(big John) when he is in trouble, only Dennis and   his friends end up making things worse for Mr. Wilson.

episodes.name: The Three F's
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson disapproves of the way Dennis' school operates, So   he writes his opinion to the newspaper and spends a day at   school to observe.

episodes.name: Never Say Dye
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson attempts to dye his hair in order to look   younger for an actress he is interviewing for her life   story. However, the dye made his hair look worse and so    he cons Henry into taking his place which end in a bunch   of tangled webs.

episodes.name: The Lost Dog
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson takes in a stray dog he believes is worth a 100 dollar reward.

episodes.name: Tuxedo Trouble
episodes.overview: Dennis and his friends start up a laundry business and    clean Mr. Wilson's tuxedo, only Dennis gets Mr. Wilson's   tuxedo mixed up with other peoples.

episodes.name: Hawaiian Love Song
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson is planning to take Mrs. Wilson to Hawaii. But when   Mr. Wilson has the plane tickets mailed to the Mitchell's,   Alice thinks Henry is taking her to Hawaii.

episodes.name: The Lucky Rabbit's Foot
episodes.overview: Dennis has what he thinks is a lucky rabbit's foot, Mr. Wilson   tricks Dennis into letting him borrow it because he thinks it   will bring him good luck.

episodes.name: Listen to the Mockingbird
episodes.overview: Mr. Wilson has a mockingbird in his yard which is keeping   him awake every night, So he takes the birds nest out of   the tree.

episodes.name: First Editions
episodes.overview: When Dennis takes his comic books over to show Mr. Wilson,   Mr. Wilson writes an important phone number on one of the   comics, So when Dennis leaves and takes his comic books Mr. Wilson spends all day looking for the comic book he wrote the phone number on.

episodes.name: A Man Among Men
episodes.overview: Dennis wants to be a grown man for a day while his dad is   out of town, So all day he does what he thinks his dad   normally does.

episodes.name: Aunt Emma Visits the Wilsons
episodes.overview: When Mr. Wilson's Aunt Emma pays a visit she takes an instant liking to Dennis, causing Mr. Wilson to fear she will make Dennis her heir.
